<HEADLINE> S. African FM Urges Closer Pak-S.African Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Visiting South African Foreign
Minister Alfred B. Nzo emphasized here today the need for more
closer political and economic relations between Pakistan and South
Africa.
</P>
<P>
While addressing the National Institute of Strategic Studies on
the topic of "Development in South and Southern Africa and the
Challenges of the 21st Century, a Perspective", Nzo said, "the
relations between Pakistan and South Africa are growing and there
is still much potential for them to grow further".
</P>
<P>
Nzo, who is on a four-day visit to Pakistan at the invitation
of his Pakistani counterpart Gohar Ayub Khan, described his visit
as part of the process of strengthening the existing friendly
relations between Pakistan and South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Nzo said that his visit would help further cement the cordial
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
South Africa would extend its support to Pakistan to become the
member of the proposed "Indian Ocean Rim Association for Regional
Cooperation".
</P>
<P>
Nzo expressed his thanks to Pakistan for extending support to
the South African people during their struggle for independence
against apartheid rule.
</P>
<P>
He said, his country believes in nuclear non-proliferation and
would extend its support to all the struggles aimed at getting rid
of this menace. He hoped that the efforts for disarmament must go
ahead.  
</P>
</TEXT>
