<HEADLINE> Downer Defends Australia's Hong Kong Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Australian Foreign Minister
Alexander Downer issued statement today, pledging support to Hong
Kong's smooth return to China.
</P>
<P>
Australia was no longer dependent on Britain and the United
States for its foreign policy and had made up its own mind about
Hong Kong, Downer said in Melbourne.
</P>
<P>
"Australia is independent and is proudly independent," Downer
said.
</P>
<P>
"Gone are the days when we just simply did what the U.S. and
the U.K. said. We now stand up for our own interests in our
region.... We have to make our own name and make our own future,"
the foreign minister said.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that he had taken this attitude to underline the
support of the Australian government for the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
"It is not in anybody's interests that the HKSAR begins its
life in controversy," he said.
</P>
<P>
Australia, a country with an extensive stake in Hong Kong, will
do all it can to ensure a successful and smooth transition in Hong
Kong, so as to show its support and understanding at this
important time, Downer added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
