<HEADLINE> S. African FM Calls on Pak President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Visiting South African Foreign
Minister Alfred B. Nzo today called on Pakistani President Farooq
Leghari and the two exchanged views on a wide range of subjects.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, President Leghari emphasized the need to
further expand trade and economic relations between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Leghari said that Pakistan was a major window of opportunity to
the resource-rich Central Asian nations and invited entrepreneurs
from South Africa to take advantage of the enormous economic
potential which the region offered through joint ventures with
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
In the regional context, Leghari spoke about Pakistan's desire
to have tension-free and good-neighborly relations with India.
</P>
<P>
This, he said, could only be possible if the core issue of
Kashmir which bedeviled relations between the two countries was
resolved in a peaceful manner and in accordance with the U.N.
Security Council Resolutions and the wishes of the people of Jammu
and Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
On the Afghan issue, Leghari emphasized Pakistan's strong
commitment to peace and stability in the war-ravaged country.
</P>
<P>
Nzo expressed the hope that exchange of visits would strengthen
the existing relations between the two countries. He said South
Africa hoped that Pakistan and India will be able to resolve the
problems between them through peaceful manners.  
</P>
</TEXT>
