<HEADLINE> Current Year's Revenue Receipts Estimated at </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's total revenue
receipts during 1996-97 fiscal year are estimated at 388.704
billion rupees (9.72 billion US dollars) as against the targeted
454.072 billion rupees (11.34 billion dollars), indicating a
shortfall of 65.37 billion rupees (1.63 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
This was stated by Finance Minister Sartaj Aziz while
presenting the national budget for 1997-98 at the National
Assembly this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
According to the finance minister, the revenue collection
target for the new financial year has been set at 450.213 billion
rupees (11.25 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
Aziz said that out of the total revenue receipts of the fiscal
year of 1996-97, the tax collection amounted to 286 billion rupees
(7.15 billion dollars) as against the target of 336.28 billion
rupees (8.4 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
The surcharge and non-tax receipts stood at 24.974 billion
rupees (624 million dollars) and 77.730 billion rupees (1.94
billion dollars) respectively as against the targets of 26.298
billion rupees (657 million dollars) and 91.4998 billion rupees
(about 2.28 billion dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
