<HEADLINE> Romanian Cargo Vessel Sunk Off S.African Coast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 13 (Xinhua) -- A Romanian cargo vessel, The
Calarasi, has sunk in choppy high seas off Port St Johns in the
Transkei, South Africa, after losing engine power on Friday
morning, said a source reaching here.
</P>
<P>
A May Day signal was received via Durban Radio when the ship
ran into trouble about ten nautical miles off Port St Johns, said
the source.
</P>
<P>
Twelve crewmen were airlifted to safety by South African Air
Force rescuers after they were found floating in a dinghy not far
from where the ship went down, said Captain Joy Rautenbach of the
Maritime Rescue Co-ordinating Centre in Cape Town.
</P>
<P>
The survivors were taken by Oryx Helicopter to Port St Johns
by late afternoon while the search for the remaining nine seamen
continued, said Rautenbach.
</P>
<P>
Swells of up to 14 metres, poor visibility and a cloud base of
900 feet hampered the air force search for the missing vessel, he
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
