<HEADLINE> hae061366 - Sports Leaders Share Views on Sports Marketing in HK Seminar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Over 450 sports leaders from
around the world and influential figures from the corporate
sectors gathered here on Friday for the opening of the "Marketing
of Sports in the 21st Century" Conference.
</P>
<P>
Eleven speakers from Australia, China, South Korea, Malaysia
and Hong Kong are invited to the two-day Conference, one of the
region's largest ever sporting seminars. The Conference is held
to let the participants share their views on sports marketing
opportunities in China's mainland and Hong Kong, the marketing of
athletes and teams, the packaging of sports programs as well as
the marketing of major Games.
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony was officiated by the Chief Secretary and
Patron of the Conference Anson Chan, along with John Hung,
chairman of the organizer Hong Kong Sports Development Board
(SDB), and representatives of the co-organizers, Amy Chan,
Executive Director of the Hong Kong tourist Association and
William Lee, President of the Hong Kong Dragon Boat Association.
</P>
<P>
"A well-structured sports system, coupled with professional
management and marketing strategies, will not only enhance the
well-being of the general public, but also exert high economic,
social and political impact to the community as a whole," Hung
said in his welcoming speech.
</P>
<P>
"Sports sponsorship, a vital component within the sports
marketing mix, creates benefits for all. Business improves the
profile, athletes better their performances, top international
events can be staged and spectators can watch sport at its very
best. Everyone is a winner," he said.
</P>
<P>
Among the speakers are Wei Jizhong, Secretary-general of the
Chinese Olympic Committee, and Michael Payne, Marketing Director
of the International Olympic Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
