<HEADLINE> Keep Vigilance against Plot on Tibet: Nepali King </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Nepali King Birendra said here
today that western countries want to make use of the Tibetan issue
and the Dalai Lama to create confusion and misunderstanding, and
China and Nepal should keep vigilance against this.
</P>
<P>
The Nepali King made these remarks when meeting with a visiting
Chinese military delegation at the Royal Palace.
</P>
<P>
Noting that Chinese President Jiang Zemin had paid a successful
visit to Nepal last year, King Birendra said he hopes the friendly
relations between Nepal and China will be maintained and
strengthened and carried on to the next generation.
</P>
<P>
He said all parties in Nepal believe that to maintain the best
relations with China is in Nepal's interests.
</P>
<P>
The king said he was glad to see Hong Kong's upcoming return to
China.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Lt. General Liao Xilong, head of the
Chinese military delegation, conveyed the cordial regards for King
Birendra from Chinese President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
And King Birendra asked Liao to convey his cordial regards to
President Jiang Zemin and other Chinese leaders.
</P>
<P>
Liao said the delegation's visit to Nepal aims to promote
understanding and develop friendship.
</P>
<P>
He said there are no problems left over by history between
China and Nepal and as bilateral relations get further
strengthened, relations between the two armed forces develop as
well.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation arrived here Thursday for a five-day
visit to Nepal at the invitation of the Royal Nepalese Army.
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit ever to Nepal by a high-level Chinese
military delegation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
