<HEADLINE> Cinema Fire Toll Rises to 50 in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Over 50 people were killed and
about 200 injured in a stampede triggered by a devastating fire
that swept through a packed cinema hall during a matinee show in a
posh New Delhi area today, the Press Trust of India said.
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out at 17:10 hours local time.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 100 firemen fought for over two hours to control the
blaze suspected to have been caused by a transformer blast in the
basement of the theater.
</P>
<P>
The toll is likely to go up as a number of injured have been
taken to various hospitals in serious condition across the city.
</P>
<P>
police claimed that the toll could have been much higher but
for the fact that the ushers quickly opened the four exit gates.
</P>
<P>
Police said oil in the transformer led to rapid spread of the
blaze. Twenty-four vehicles parked in the cinema campus were
gutted in the fire.  
</P>
</TEXT>
