<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angola Needs Five Years to Eradicate Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- It will take Angola at least five
years to rid itself of poverty, Bernard Ntegeye, resident
representative in Angola of the United Nations Development
Program (UNDP), said here in Luanda today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to press circles on occasion of issuing a human
development report for 1997 by the UNDP, Ntegeye said that the
human development index in Angola has increased from 0.283 in
1996 to 0.337 in 1997, and the prospect to raise social welfare
is very broad. This plus Angola's vast territory and rich natural
resources will enable the country eradicate its poverty in a
short period of time, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, to eradicate poverty, some prerequisites are also
required, such as the consolidation of peace, the restoration of
war damaged infrastructures, the reconstruction of the country
and an explicit policy and plan for eradicating poverty, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The UNDP will work together with the Angolan statistical
bureau for the publication of a report on the poverty situation
of the country as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that over 60 percent of the people in the
country were living in dire poverty in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
