<HEADLINE> Anti-Army Worm Campaign Launched in Ethiopia's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Spraying of pesticide against
army-worm infestation which broke out in seven districts of the
Amhara region is well underway, the Ethiopian News Agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to the regional agricultural bureau, the pesticide
has been sprayed over 139 hectares of land with a view to
protecting crops such as maize, sorghum and millet against the
pest.
</P>
<P>
The bureau said 36,800 kg of pesticide and 470 spraying
equipment will not be sufficient if the weather remains conducive
for the breeding of the army-worm.
</P>
<P>
The bureau called on administrative bodies and agricultural
professionals to actively involve in the campaign and said aid
organizations active in the region should render extra spraying
appliances and transportation facilities in the effort to
containing the plague. 
</P>
</TEXT>
