<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Chief Believes in Future of Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 13 (Xinhua) -- UN Secretary-General Kofi
Annan said here today that Hong Kong will continue to be dynamic
economic and financial center as it has been until now.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview with Xinhua, Annan said that China's
policy of "one country, two systems" toward Hong Kong is a very
wise policy, which allows Hong Kong to operate the way it has
done.
</P>
<P>
With the policy of "one country, two systems" to be applied in
Hong Kong, everybody will gain -- the people live in Hong Kong and
other parts of China and the people in the rest of the world, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Since China's economy is dynamic and China itself goes through
progressive and dynamic changes, Hong Kong will remain a dynamic
center.
</P>
<P>
On Chinese government resuming the exercise of sovereignty over
Hong Kong on coming July 1, he said it is a historical occasion.
He himself will be there to witness the transfer of power.
</P>
<P>
On the smooth transition of power, he said that the Chinese and
British governments have handled the issue very well and set a
good example for other regions to solve disputes through dialogue
and discussions.
</P>
<P>
"It is always better to settle the territorial question through
dialogue and negotiation rather than through military means," he
stressed.
</P>
<P>
As there are a lot of conflicts over territory and over
boarder, he stressed, "It has also set a good example for other
regions of the world to realize that it is possible to solve
disputes through dialogue and discussions."
</P>
<P>
He noted that in addition to Hong Kong, Macao will also become
a part of China in a few years.
</P>
<P>
"These are historical developments managed in peaceful and
political manner. I think it is a good lesson for the rest of the
world. I applaud the Chinese authorities for their patience" in
solution of the historical issues, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
