<HEADLINE> Turkey Withdraws Ambassador From Libya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Turkey today announced the
withdrawal of its Ambassador to Tripoli Ates Balkan to protest
Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi's "provocative" statements against
Ankara.
</P>
<P>
A Foreign Ministry statement said that this decision will not
affect the friendship with Libya, but calling Tripoli to
appreciate "the values of countries who are friends to Libya."
</P>
<P>
Addressing public in northern coastal city of Derna Wednesday,
Gaddafi said the Turkish army is ruled by Jews and Prime Minister
Necmettin Erbakan is not aware that the Turkish army has carried
out a cross-border military operation in northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Launching condemnation, Turkish deputy Prime Minister and
Foreign Minister Tansu Ciller said "Gaddafi's inappropriate
expressions are not in harmony with the rules of respect and
politeness of international relations."
</P>
<P>
"We strongly regret Gaddafi's expressions," she said.
</P>
