<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania Telecommunications Commpany to Get </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 13 (Xinhua) -- A contract was signed on
Tuesday between the Tanzania Telecommunications Company Ltd.
(TTCL) and the Dar es Salaam-based firm, Soft-Tech Consultants
Ltd, under which the Soft-Tech Consultants Ltd will provide for
TTCL a new service order and billing system.
</P>
<P>
In a statement here today, TTCL Acting Public Relations
Manager, Gad Mkemwa, said that the contract worth 3,969,105 U.S.
Dollars would be implemented for one year.
</P>
<P>
Mkemwa said the new computer billing system will help provide
payment of bills at any TTCL customer service center and that the
bills will be accurate.
</P>
<P>
"The billing system will interface with a database network,
therefore eliminating the need for physical transfer of billing
data on paper to the billing center," he added. 
</P>
