<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Two Loans for Brazil Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today announced
the approval of two loans totaling 54.6 million U.S. dollars
equivalent for Brazil's projects.
</P>
<P>
First loan of some 45 million dollars is earmarked for the
privatization project in the Mato Grosso state. The project which
is estimated to have a total cost of 281 million dollars is aimed
to eliminate a considerable burden from state finances and improve
the delivery of basic services to the population.
</P>
<P>
Another loan of about 9.6 million dollars will be used to
finance a Water Resources Management Pilot Project in the
drought-plagued state of Ceara.
</P>
<P>
The project will develop, test, and evaluate various
methodologies to help implement integrated water resources
management of river basins. It will facilitate a future project
that will improve the access to water for the rural poor and urban
population in the state that suffers from cyclical drought.
</P>
