<HEADLINE> 11 Candidates to Contest in Liberian Presidential </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The Liberian electoral commission
announced that 11 candidates,including three former warlords, are
to contest in the country's presidential elections scheduled for
July 19.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here today said that the official campaign
for the presidential and legislative polls will kick off on June
16, and close on July 18.
</P>
<P>
The commission was also quoted as saying that other
presidential aspirants still have the chance to declare their
intentions until midnight Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Among the 11 candidates are three key players in the Liberian
civil war that has killed more than 150,000 people and left more
others homeless since December 1989.
</P>
<P>
They are Charles Taylor of the National Patriotic Party,
Alhaji Kromah of the All Liberia Coalition Party and George Boley
of the National Democratic Party of Liberia.
</P>
<P>
Ellen Johnson Sirleaf of the Unity Party is the only woman
candidate.
</P>
<P>
Others in the presidential race are Cletus Wotorson, Gabriel
Baccus Matthews, Chea Cheapoo, Togba-Nah Tipoteh, Harry Moniba,
Boima Fahnbulleh and Martin Sherif.
</P>
<P>
Liberian presidential and parliamentary elections were
originally set for May 30 this year by the revised Abuja peace
accord signed by the warring factions in August 1996, in Nigeria.
They were, however, shifted to July 19 at the extra-ordinary
summit of the Committee of Nine on Liberia of the Economic
Community of West African States held in Abuja on May 21. 
</P>
</TEXT>
