<DOCNO> XIE19970614.0055 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> European Shares Hit Record Highs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Shares on Europe's major stock
markets hit an all-time high today.
</P>
<P>
Britain's FTSE-100 index was driven to its third record close
this week by the U.S. stock market's rise and by fresh domestic
bid activity which helped boost investor confidence. The FTSE-100
closed at 4,783.1, up 25.7 points. This was up 161.80 from last
Friday.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, equities ended trade at a record closing high,
lifted by Wall Street's strongest bull run in history and after a
firm dollar propelled the equity market higher. The DAX-30 index
closed at 3,744.44, up 36.45 points. This was up 49.15 on the
week.
</P>
<P>
The Paris bourse surged 1.75 percent to close at an all-time
high. Traders said comments from the German-French summit, which
made progress on a European Union budget stability pact, helped
push up the market. The CAC-40 index closed up 48.25 points at
2,808.52, a rise of 89.27 from last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
