<HEADLINE> Michalczewski to Give up a Boxing Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Newly crowned WBO, IBF and WBA light
heavyweight champion Dariusz Michalczewski will give up one of his
titles within the week, his promoter said in Duesseldorf, Germany,
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The German became the first man in history to own the WBA, IBF
and WBO titles in his weight class with a stunning 12-round upset
of Virgil Hill Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Michalczewski, the undefeated WBO champion, took away the other
two titles from Hill by pounding out a unanimious one-sided
decision over the American.
</P>
<P>
But the German's promoter, Klaus-Peter Kohl, said Michalczewski
may give up the IBF title since No. 1 challenger William Guthrie
has won a court ruling for a championship fight by July 19th.
</P>
<P>
Michalczewski also doesn't want to fight twice within 45 days,
the promoter added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
