<HEADLINE> Large Hand-Woven Carpet Laid in Hong Kong Hall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 14 (Xinhua) -- A large hand-woven carpet, 14
meters in length and width, has been laid in the Hall of Hong Kong
inside the Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
The 196-sq-meter carpet, which has no seams, is the largest of
the kind in China.
</P>
<P>
The carpet, woven with more than 2,000 kg of grey wool and some
pink wool, is both modern and elegant.
</P>
<P>
Some 20 technicians and workers at the Beijing No.1 Carpet
Factory, using a special steel frame, have worked for three months
to complete the carpet, which was presented by the factory as a
gift for the return of Hong Kong on July 1.
</P>
<P>
"It must not have been an easy job to complete such a
high-quality carpet in such a short time," said Prof. Wang Weiyu,
the designer of the Hall of Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
