<HEADLINE> Beijing Holds Cultural Activities Along Chang'an Avenue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 14 (Xinhua) -- A variety of cultural activities
were held tonight at eight locations along the Chinese capital
city's biggest street, Chang'An, which means "eternal peace," to
mark the country's tourism blitz for 1997.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Qian Qichen attended the opening ceremony and
watched this evening's events.
</P>
<P>
The shows were held in the front of eight buildings, extending
from the blocks of Jianguomen to Fuxingmen along the street.
</P>
<P>
The highlight of the evening was staged at the Chang'An
Guanghua Building, where singers and dancers of the national and
municipal troupes put on a show.
</P>
<P>
Municipal leaders, top officials of the Ministry of Culture and
the National Tourism Administration joined a crowd of thousands to
watch the performance. 
</P>
