<DOCNO> XIE19970614.0066 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gala Charity Dinner Marks Completion of HKCEC Extension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 14 (Xinhua) -- A gala charity dinner catering
2,800 people was held here today to celebrate the completion of
the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center (HKCEC) Extension,
the venue for the handover ceremony at midnight on June 30.
</P>
<P>
Jointly organized by the Hong Kong Trade Development Council
(HKTDC), the Community Chest of Hong Kong and the HKCEC, the
dinner was the first major event held in the extension.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the occasion, HKTDC Chairman Dr Victor Fung said,
"Little more than three years ago, where you are all sitting was a
tract of water. In those three years, under millions of pairs of
watchful eyes, we have created a new landmark for our city."
</P>
<P>
The HKTDC was entrusted by the Hong Kong government in March
1994 to develop the 4.8-billion-HK-dollar (615 million US dollars)
project, covering reclamation and construction.
</P>
<P>
The expanded HKCEC will strengthen Hong Kong's lead as the
trade fair and convention capital of Asia well into the next
century, Fung said.
</P>
<P>
"With capacity more than doubled, we can at last meet pent-up
demand for space at the HKCEC. Overnight, we can double the size
of our largest trade fairs and accommodate many new world-class
exhibitions," he said.
</P>
<P>
Inspired by an image of a bird soaring into the sky, the
low-rise complex is a dramatic contrast against the backdrop of
skyscrapers on Hong Kong Island's waterfront.
</P>
<P>
"It is no accident that the architectural design for the
Extension was inspired by the power and grace of flight, a sense
of soaring. For that, truly, is how we see Hong Kong in the coming
century -- a city on the ascent, soaring confidently into the
future," Fung said.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa was invited to the 227-table
dinner, which is expected to raise some seven million HK dollars
(897,000 US dollars) for local charity services.
</P>
<P>
"Very soon, on July 1, the whole world's attention is going to
focus on this magnificent new Extension where the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region will be inaugurated," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Here is where I will be sworn in as the first Chief Executive
of HKSAR, and here is where we will witness a new dawn for Hong
Kong. This building is, indeed, a new symbol for a new era -- one
in which I believe Hong Kong will reach even greater heights,"
Tung concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
