<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Beats Becker in Halle Tennis Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Yevgeny Kafelnikov of
Russia easily defeated former Wimbledon champion Boris Becker of
Germany in the semifinals of the $875,000 Halle grasscourt tennis
tournament on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov, who ousted Germany's Michael Stich in the
quarter-finals on Friday, beat the fourth-seeded Becker 6-3 6-4 in
a 75-minute match and will now meet the winner of the second
semifinal between Paul Haarhuis and Petr Korda.
</P>
<P>
It was the first match between the two men on a grass court.
In five previous meetings, Becker had won four times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
