<HEADLINE> Oaths, Declarations (Amendment) Bill Tabled to PLC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The Oaths and Declarations
(Amendment) Bill 1997 was tabled here today at the 11th plenary
meeting of the Provisional Legislative Council (PLC) for the first
and second readings.
</P>
<P>
Introduced by Michael Suen, secretary for policy coordination
of the Chief Executive's Office of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR), the bill seeks to implement through
 local legislation the provision in Article 104 of the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
Under that provision, when assuming office, the chief
executive, principal officials, members of the Executive and
Legislative Councils of the HKSAR and judges and other members of
the HKSAR judiciary will have to swear to uphold the Basic Law and
 swear allegiance to the HKSAR of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Suen said the bill has repealed the colonial oaths and
formulated appropriate oaths in accordance with the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
According to Suen, the new oaths are based on the related
decisions made by the Preparatory Committee of the HKSAR last
month.
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
</TEXT>
