<HEADLINE> ASEAN Economic Ministers Push for Realization of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The ASEAN economic ministers'
informal meeting here today produced a set of recommendations for
the regional grouping's economic strategy in facing the year 2020.
</P>
<P>
Indonesian Coordinating Minister for Production and
Distribution Hartarto Sastrosoenarto told the press after the
meeting that the recommendations will be taken up in the second
informal ASEAN leaders' summit in Kuala Lumpur in December.
</P>
<P>
He said today's four-hour ministerial meeting focused on how to
carry out continuous and progressive economic cooperation among
the ASEAN countries.
</P>
<P>
The first informal ASEAN summit in Jakarta in December last
year produced the 'ASEAN Vision 2020' and the 'ASEAN Common
Investment Area.'
</P>
<P>
"This morning's meeting aimed to push for the realization of
the ASEAN Vision 2020 and the ASEAN Common Investment Area," he
said.
</P>
<P>
"We have to formulate clear steps leading to the ASEAN Vision
2020, particularly on how to deal with the ever tightening
competition in trade, industry and investment," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Hartarto also said that the economic recommendations will be
consolidated with the social and political recommendations which
will be submitted also to the next ASEAN informal summit in Kuala
Lumpur where the ASEAN 30th anniversary will be formally
celebrated.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN economic ministers will meet again in Kuala Lumpur in
July for the formal ASEAN economic ministerial meeting (AEM) and
in October for the ASEAN Free Trade Area (AFTA) Council meeting,
also in Kuala Lumpur.
</P>
<P>
In the AFTA meeting, the ASEAN economic ministers will meet
with delegations of Japan's Ministry for Trade and Industry (MITI)
and the Australia-New Zealand Closer Economic Relation (CER)
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia, Laos and Myanmar, the grouping's new members, will
also send their representatives to the meeting, Hartarto said.
