<HEADLINE> HK PLC Passes Motion for Supporting Judges Nominees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The Provisional Legislative
Council (PLC) of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) today passed a motion supporting the proposal to appoint
three permanent judges of the Court of Final Appeal (CFA) and the
chief judge of the High Court of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
The motion was tabled by Elsie Leung Oi-sie, secretary of
justice of the HKSAR, at the 11th meeting of the PLC held in
Shenzhen, a South China city adjacent to Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
On June 12, the Judicial Officers Recommendation Commission
(Designate) recommended that Henry Litton, Charles Ching and Kemal
 Bokhary be appointed CFA permanent judges and Patrick Chan be
appointed chief judge of the High Court of the HKSAR on July 1
this year.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the PLC meeting this afternoon, Leung said that with
 PLC members' support for the proposed appointments, all five key
posts in the HKSAR judiciary would have been filled by the most
capable and suitable candidates.
</P>
<P>
The five key posts refer to CFA's chief justice and three
permanent judges as well as the chief judge of the High Court.
</P>
<P>
On May 24, the PLC passed a motion to support the appointment
of Andrew Li as the chief justice of the CFA.
</P>
<P>
Leung noted that Article 93 of the Basic Law provides that
judges and other members of the judiciary serving in Hong Kong
before the establishment of the HKSAR may all remain in
employment.
</P>
<P>
"Steps are being taken to ensure the continued employment of
all serving judges and judicial officers," she said, adding that
with such a line-up, the HKSAR Judiciary and Hong Kong's legal
system are not only assured of a smooth transition, but also
poised to continue the development of the common law in Hong Kong
in the new and challenging era ahead.  
</P>
