<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State Council to Ensure Smooth Purchasing of Summer Grain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The General Office of the State
Council, China's Cabinet, has issued a circular to further ensure
the smooth purchasing of summer grain across the country.
</P>
<P>
Governments at all levels should strictly abide by the policy
worked out by the State Council, and all summer grain within the
fixed quotas should be purchased at the same price level as that
of last year, the circular said.
</P>
<P>
Once the fixed-quota purchasing is completed, the units should
go on actively organizing the purchasing of summer grain at a
negotiable price.
</P>
<P>
The grain risk funds jointly set up by the central and local
governments should play a big role in regulating and controlling
the buying. All price differences resulting from protecting
farmers' and consumers' interests should be covered by the funds.
</P>
<P>
The funds will also encourage the purchasing of summer grain at
reasonable prices for farmers, if the market prices are lower than
the ordered prices.
</P>
<P>
Plans should be made to ensure the supply and good management
of purchasing funds for summer grain and edible oil. The circular
calls for the establishment of responsibility systems in
governments at all levels to collect the purchasing fund, and none
of the purchasing fund is allowed to be spent for other purposes.
</P>
<P>
The circular also placed emphasis on the need for spacious
storehouses and the smooth transportation of the purchased summer
grain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
