<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Underwater Telecom Cable to Be Built in South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 14 (Xinhua) -- A second underwater
telecommunications cable linking south China's island province of
Hainan with the country's inland areas is to be built during the
second half this year.
</P>
<P>
The 301-km line, to be built at a cost of nearly 200 million
yuan, will link Haikou, capital of Hainan Province, with Beihai, a
coastal city in south Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Construction is expected to be completed in 1998, and will
bring an increase of 34,000 telecom lines to Hainan.
</P>
<P>
The line will join with the country's two major telecom trunks,
which run north to south and east to west.
</P>
<P>
The first underwater telecom cable linking the island and
inland extends from Haikou to Zhanjiang in Guangdong Province.
</P>
</TEXT>
