<HEADLINE> US Resolution Encourages Israeli Aggression: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. resolution to recognize
Jerusalem as the capital of Israel and to move the U.S. embassy
from Tel Aviv to the city is aimed at encouraging Israeli
aggression, the local Syrian daily Teshreen said today.
</P>
<P>
The paper pointed out in its commentary that the resolution
does not affect the identity of Jerusalem in the least but it
has adverse effects on the Middle East peace process and the
credibility of the United States as well as its interests in the
region.
</P>
<P>
The resolution, which was adopted by the U.S. House of
Representatives Wednesday, approved the allocation of 100
million U.S. dollars to move the U.S. embassy from Tel Aviv to
Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The paper lashed at the U.S. House of Representatives for
legalizing the Israeli occupation, terming the United States as
defender of the Jewish state and the Israeli aggressive designs
in complete violation of moral principles and conventions.
</P>
<P>
Jerusalem is an Arab territory that is not subject to the
decisions of the U.S. House of Representatives or the Israeli
Knesset (parliament), the paper added.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said that "we have never heard of a legislative
house in a foreign country legalizing the occupation and
usurpation of the territories of another country as is the case in
the occupied Arab territories."
</P>
<P>
Jerusalem is an Arab land and will remain so regardless of
Israel's whims, the daily concluded.
</P>
<P>
The Israelis claim the controversial city of Jerusalem as its
"undivided" capital while the Palestinians want it to be the
capital of their future independent state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
