<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Both the Party building in
colleges and the ethics education in middle and primary schools
should be improved to meet China's development needs, a top Party
official told participants in two national conferences, which were
concluded here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the joint closing meeting of the Sixth National
Conference on Party building in colleges and another conference on
ethics education in middle and primary schools, Zhang Quanjing,
director of the Organization Department of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China, said that the work to strengthen
the Party in colleges should closely follow the rules for the
Party organizations at the grassroots level.
</P>
<P>
Liu bin, vice-director of the State Education Commission, noted
that practical measures should be taken according to the real
conditions in middle and primary schools across the country to
promote ethics education.
</P>
<P>
The measures include separating the sum allotted for ethics
education from the overall education fund, training a group of
experts and high-quality teachers for ethics instruction, and
improving the ethics of teachers themselves and raising the living
standard of ethics teachers, Liu said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, ethics teachers should increase their social
awareness, learn more about the their field of study, and improve
their teaching styles, he said. 
