<HEADLINE> TDC Leader Briefs on Completion of HK CEC Extension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Viktor Fung, chairman of the
Hong Kong Trade Development Council (TDC), stressed here today
that Hong Kong's newest landmark is the dramatic extension to the
Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center (HKCEC).
</P>
<P>
At a news briefing held in the HKCEC this afternoon, Fung
said: "Just three years ago, where we are all standing now, was
water -- a part of the harbor. Now it is the largest, and finest,
conference and exhibition facility in Asia."
</P>
<P>
From a tract of water to a building three times the size of the
Sydney Opera House, it took the TDC just 39 months to complete
the extension project, he said, adding that the new facility, on
a man-made island off the harborfront of Wanchai, more than
doubles the capacity of the nine-year-old HKCEC.
</P>
<P>
"Over the next few weeks this building will have an opportunity
to make a lasting impression on the world. As the site for the
handover ceremonies, it is destined to become one of the most
visible and recognizable structures on earth," Fung pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The expanded HKCEC was selected as the venue serving for
ceremonies marking the return of Hong Kong to the motherland and
the establishment of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region. It is also scheduled to house the annual meetings of the
World Bank/IMF in September this year.
</P>
<P>
"We have met the deadline. We have completed the task on
time. And on Budget as we promised," Fung said. The reclamation
and extension project of 615-million U.S. dollars was entrusted
by the Hong Kong government to the TDC, Hong Kong's statutory
organization for promoting trade.
</P>
<P>
"Because of the efforts of many people, the world will see Hong
Kong at its best," he continued. "They will see a city already
moving confidently beyond 1997 and into the 21st century."
</P>
<P>
According to him, some 400 companies from over 30 countries and
regions participated in the construction work of the extension
project.
</P>
<P>
With the HKCEC, which generates billions of dollars in direct
and indirect benefit to the economy each year, the TDC has
strengthened Hong Kong's lead as the trade fair and meetings
capital of Asia. It organizes more than 20 international trade
fairs and exhibitions in Hong Kong annually.  
</P>
</TEXT>
