<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-14 09:45 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan's Paper Closes down due to New Press Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The Jordanian satirical weekly
newspaper of Abed Rabbo has decided to close after making
its last stab today, becoming the first victim of the new Press
and Publication Law introduced last month.
</P>
<P>
Abed Rabbo's chief editor Youssef Ghishan said, in the last
issue published today, that the administrators of the paper,
after only 45 issues of publication in 10 months, have chosen
to close it because they could not afford the fines imposed by
the new press law.
</P>
<P>
"The new law is elastic, and it can be applied to almost any
article we publish. The law can be interpreted in any way," the
chief editor said.
</P>
<P>
The provisions of the new law impose fines ranging from
30,000 to 50,000 Jordanian dinars (about 42,373 to 70,621
U.S. dollars) and oblige the papers, both dailies and weeklies,
to raise their capital.
</P>
<P>
It is not the capital requirements, but the huge fines that
concerns Abed Rabbo, said Ghishan.
</P>
<P>
Abed Rabbo's status as a satirical paper and the "elasticity"
of the law will expose it to the potential of sustaining heavy
financial penalties which it can not afford, he added.
</P>
<P>
The law offers an extended list of issues that can not be
covered in news stories, editorials or cartoons. The government
has justified the law by saying that a new law was necessary
after officials, parliamentarians, citizens and journalists
complained that the weekly press often had exceeded the limits
of public decency in dealing with many issues.
</P>
<P>
Ghishan asserted that a satirical paper is a special breed of
press which "needs a wider range of freedom than a regular
newspaper."
</P>
<P>
"But the new law does not provide that," he added.
</P>
<P>
Abed Rabbo circulates about 20,000 copies weekly in Jordan
and an undisclosed number in countries like the United Arab
Emirates, Lebanon, Oman, Greece, Egypt and the United States.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970614.0113 </DOCNO>
