<HEADLINE> 4.8 Million Nigerians Hypertensive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 14 (Xinhua) -- About 4.8 million Nigerians are
hypertensive, the official "New Nigerian" said today.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted a material of the Foundation Medical
Center as saying that hypertension and its complications kill
more adult Nigerians than any other diseases.
</P>
<P>
It said before the age of 35, less than one person in every 20
Nigerians suffers hypertension, but after the age 35, the disease
occurs in about one person in five.
</P>
<P>
The report advised hypertensive patients to abstain from
excessive intake of salt, drinking and smoking. They should also
reduce the quantity of food they eat and exercise regularly.
</P>
</TEXT>
