<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- France and Germany Friday failed to adopt a common position
on the budgetary stability pact of the future European single
currency countries. Only 48 hours remained for the French and
German leaders to reach a compromise before the EU Amsterdam
summit in Madrid which is expected to ratify the pact.
</P>
<P>
-- A de facto truce began Friday between the two warring sides
of the Congo Republic due to exterior pressure. Both sides accused
each other of being responsible for the violence which devastated
Brazzaville in a feud for power. The new fighting might be caused
by the planned withdrawal of French troops, which have completed
evacuation of foreigners.
