</P>
<P>
-- Despite a joint will to de-dramatize their dispute over the
budgetary stability pact for the future European single currency,
France and Germany Friday failed to find a rapprochement of points
of view on the pact at the Franco-German summit in Poitiers.
</P>
<P>
French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin, meeting with with
Chancellor Helmut Kohl respectively during the summit, hardened
his position by insisting on a social chapter in the pact and a
greater coordination in economic policies by European Union member
countries.
</P>
<P>
-- The public prosecutor's office of Paris Friday opened an
investigation against X for accused electoral fraud in the
constituency of Paris during the legislative elections. 
</P>
