<HEADLINE> Brazil Beats Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Brazil, backed by Rolando's two
goals and Romario's one, trounced Costa Rica 5-0 Friday in the
second match in Group C of the Copa America in Santa Cruz, Bolivia.
</P>
<P>
Djalminha's free kick in 22 minutes into the game began
Brazil's goaling streak. An auto goal by Costa Rica's Ronald
Gonzalez 37 minutes into the game was followed by two more by
Ronaldo, 49 and 52 minutes into the game. Romario scored the
game's last goal seven minutes later, said reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica tried in vain to score, despite several nice plays
and shots. But Brazil's super team controlled the field.
</P>
<P>
Mexico beat Colombia 2-1 earlier in the evening. It is also
members of Group C. With Friday's victory, Mexico and Brazil have
harvested three points and Colombia and Costa Rica none.  
