<HEADLINE> Tanzania, Zambia Sign Power Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania and Zambia on
Friday signed a memorandum of inter-governmental understanding in
the area of energy during a short ceremony in the city, local
press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Minister for Energy and Minerals
of Tanzania, Abdallah Kigoda and Minister for Energy and Water
Development of Zambia, Suresh Desai on behalf of their
governments respectively.
</P>
<P>
The agreement also covers inter-utility memorandum and general
agreement of co-operation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The agreement clears the way for building of a 650-kilometer
electricity line from Pensulo in Zambia to Mbeya in south-western
Tanzania at an estimated cost of about 130 million US Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The line will boost the Tanzania national electricity grid
with 200 megawatts.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is part of the fulfillment of the Southern
Africa Development Community (SADC) project of Southern African
Power Plant (SAPP). 
</P>
</TEXT>
