<HEADLINE> Fuel Prices Down in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's fuel prices fell by 30
Shillings (1,070 Shillings equal to one US Dollars) yesterday in
response to fuel duty reductions announced in the budget on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the local daily the New Vision today, a litre of
petrol is now 1,114 Shillings down from 1,140 Shillings, diesel
is selling at 1,000 Shillings from 1,030 Shillings, while
kerosene is now at 810 Shillings from 840 Shillings.
</P>
<P>
Finance Minister Mayanja-Nkangi in his budget speech announced
a 10 percent decrease on fuel duty for petrol, 160 percent for
diesel and 105 percent for kerosene.
</P>
<P>
It is an action taken by the government to reduce fuel
smuggling in the country.
</P>
<P>
The reduction in fuel prices come one week after fuel
companies announced their first price hike this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
