<HEADLINE> Photo Exhibition in Ecuador Marks Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, June 12 (Xinhua) -- A photo exhibition about the history
and development of Hong Kong opened here today to mark Hong Kong's
return to China.
</P>
<P>
One hundred carefully chosen photographs covering the history
of Hong Kong, exchanges between Hong Kong and the inland areas, the
process of Hong Kong's return and Kong Kong today will be
displayed at the exhibition, which ends on June 29.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is co-sponsored by the Chinese Embassy in
Ecuador and an Ecuadoran cultural organization, the Home of
Culture.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony, Yang Binwei, the Chinese
ambassador to Ecuador, said that China's resumption of the
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong is an event of epoch-making
significance in the history of China.
</P>
<P>
It sets a good example for nations in the world to peacefully
resolve the problems left over by history, Yang added.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador hopes that the exhibition can help the people of
Ecuador learn more about the changes in Hong Kong over the past
century and the history of the struggle of the Chinese people for
the return of Hong Kong and the unification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The Ecuadoran sponsor said that the return of Hong Kong to
the motherland is a happy event for the Chinese people and the
exhibition will further promote mutual understanding and
friendship between the peoples of Ecuador and China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
