<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia to Combat Outside Interference: Staff Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia's Chief of General
Staff Momcilo Perisic said here today that the Yugoslav military
opposes outside interference, and is ready to protect the
country's sovereignty and territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslav news agency Tanjug quoted him as saying at a news
conference held to mark Yugoslav Army Day today that many external
forces are attempting to pursue their own interests and goals by
trying to involve domestic elements.
</P>
<P>
He said that the war in former Yugoslavia is such an example,
which led countrymen to kill each other.
</P>
<P>
Perisic pointed out that many outside forces are still
attempting to realize their own aims by provoking internal
conflicts in Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
He warned that the Yugoslav military would do its utmost to
prevent any such attempt. 
</P>
