<HEADLINE> Agriculture Census to Start Monday in Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The Venezuelan government will
start Monday the second and last stage of a census to gather data
needed for promoting competitive agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
The 4th Agriculture and Livestock Census will be made by 350
census takers and 3,000 support staff members, Agriculture and
Livestock Minister Raul Alegrett told the press today.
</P>
<P>
Preparation for the census has taken 20 months, Alegrett said.
</P>
<P>
The field work to be carried out in the coming census will
permit the cartographic update of Venezuela's rural areas and to
know its physical structure in all aspects, said the minister.
</P>
<P>
The first Venezuelan agriculture census was made in 1936 and
the one to start Monday will be the last of this century.
</P>
<P>
Alegrett said the new census is expected to provide statistics
needed for the adoption of measures in the agriculture and
livestock sectors of the country. 
</P>
