<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fujian To Set Up Museum On China's Modern Navy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 14 (Xinhua) -- A museum on China's modern navy
will be set up in Mawei, a port city in east China's Fujian
Province, and preparations are underway.
</P>
<P>
The port was the birthplace of China's modern navy, with
China's first shipping bureau, navy school, and the first navy
fleet born in the place.
</P>
<P>
The Fuzhou shipping school, established here in 1867, has
trained a group of technical talents and navy generals for the
country, including Deng Shichang, Yan Fu, and Zhan Tianyou, who
played a big role in the development of China's modern industry
and navy.
</P>
<P>
Covering an area of 2,000 square meters, the museum will
include a reception hall, a reporting hall, and an exhibition
hall, with a total investment of 30 million yuan (about 4 million
US dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
