<HEADLINE> Sampras out of Queen's Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 13 (Xinhua) -- World number on Pete Sampras was
defeated by unseeded Swede Jonas Bjorkman Friday to crash out of
the Queen's men's tournament.
</P>
<P>
The American suffered a 3-6, 6-3, 6-4 quarter-final defeat to
the Swedish Davis Cup player.
</P>
<P>
Sampras won the first set and looked unlikely to be beaten by
the 25-year-old Bjorkman.
</P>
<P>
But Bjorkman found his form in the second set, breaking the
Sampras serve in the eighth game and surviving a torrid ninth game
with two break points to pull even.
</P>
<P>
Bjorkman broke Sampras in the first game of the third set. He
lost his own serve as Sampras drew level 4-4 then attacked again,
rushing the net and unsettling the world number one.
</P>
<P>
Bjorkman broke to 5-4 then went in for the kill. Sampras
finally went down with a weak return on match point which the
Swede punished with a backhand volley.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Greg Rusedski became the first-ever Briton to reach the
tournmanent's semifinals. He beat French Open semifinalist Patrick
Rafter of Australia 4-6, 7-5, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Mark Philippoussis of Australia also won through, beating Jens
Knippschild of Germany 6-2, 6-7, 6-4. Philippoussis will meet
Bjorkman in the semifinals while Rusedski faces either
third-seeded Croat Goran Ivanesevic or Jerome Golmard of France.
</P>
</TEXT>
