<HEADLINE> Sichuan Protects Interest of Overseas-Funded Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan
provincial government recently asked the whole province to take
further efforts to create a better investment environment.
</P>
<P>
The relevant departments in Jinjiang District of Chengdu, the
capital city of Sichuan, was found to overcharge 9,500 yuan (1,100
US dollars) from a Malaysia-funded enterprise during examinations
earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
In line with relavent regulations, the provincial government of
Sichuan instructed those departments in Jinjiang District to
apologize and return the overcharged money to the Malaysia-funded
enterprise, in addition to disqualify the examining right from
those who were involved in the case.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government also decided to keep close touch with
the Malaysia-funded enterprise and other overseas-funded
enterprises so as to prevent similar cases from happening.
</P>
<P>
"All the overseas-funded enterprises are encouraged to defend
their lawful rights and interest, and government departments at
all levels should take the responsibility to create a fair and
efficient environment for overseas-funded enterprises to operate,"
a notice released by the provincial government said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
