<HEADLINE> New Drug to Inhibit AIDS Developed in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harbin, June 14 (Xinhua) -- A pharmaceutical company here
successfully developed a medicine which is able to inhibit or even
destroy HIV virus without impairing human immune cells.
</P>
<P>
The drug, named Gongming Anti-HIV injection, is made entirely
from Chinese herbs, according to the developer Gongming
Pharmaceutical Company based here in Harbin, capital city of
northeast China's Heilongjiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Test report by the AIDS testing and diagnosing lab of the
Chinese People's Liberation Army Medical Research Institute has
affirmed that the drug is effective "to a certain degree" in
inhibiting HIV, the virus that causes deadly AIDS. And the
authoritative medical institute decides to put the medicine into
clinical practice. 
</P>
