<HEADLINE> Tianjin Becomes Favorite Place For Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Overseas businesses have found
north China's port city of Tianjin an ideal place to invest, as
most of them are making good profits there.
</P>
<P>
The foreign-funded joint ventures in Tianjin scored 25.9
billion yuan in sales during the first four months of this year, a
year-on-year increase of 30 percent, with their profits up by 34
percent.
</P>
<P>
Motorola (China) Electronic Limited Company started its
business in Tianjin in 1988 with 300,000 US dollars, and has now
invested more than one billion US dollars in China. It produced 16
billion yuan worth of sales last year, with 2.86 billion yuan in
profit.
</P>
<P>
His company has made remarkable progress, and doubled its sales
volume over the past two years, said Mr. Pierre Tabary, general
manager of the Merlin Gerin Company, Ltd., Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Lucrative prospects encouraged 181 foreign-funded enterprises
to increase 770 million US dollars of investment in Tianjin last
year. Based in the city, a Taiwan foodstuff company has set up
seven production bases across the country, with annual sales worth
2.4 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
A coastal city, Tianjin enjoys convenient transportation,
favorable policies for overseas investment and efficient services,
serving as the best springboard onto north China's market, said Ye
Disheng, vice mayor of the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
