<HEADLINE> North China Province Upgrading State Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 14 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
is using more and more overseas investment to upgrade its
poorly-performing state enterprises, in a move to enhance its
economic strength.
</P>
<P>
Hebei has been implementing a plan to use overseas financing to
speed up technological development in the local 1,154 state
enterprises during the 1995-1997 period. Over the past two years,
it has funded 794 technology-upgrading projects with overseas
investment.
