<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Navy Expands Exchanges Worldwide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese navy has increased
exchanges with its counterparts throughout the world, sources with
the navy say.
</P>
<P>
Since the country's reform and opening-up in the late 1970s,
China's navy has received naval officials from more than 20
countries.
</P>
<P>
The visiting of warships between countries is becoming more
common internationally; early this year, two Chinese naval fleets
paid visits to countries in America and Southeast Asia, attracting
world attention.
</P>
<P>
Since 1985, 21 Chinese naval ships, in 11 groups, have toured
14 countries, publicizing China's independent foreign policy of
peace, illustrating the navy's image and boosting ties with the
navies in visited countries.
</P>
<P>
In turn, the Chinese navy has received more than 60 visiting
warships from 20 countries since 1980. The United States sends the
most naval vessels to visit China; so far, eight warships have
come in four separate groups.
</P>
<P>
In addition, China's navy has conducted more technological and
academic exchanges with its counterparts in other
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
