<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Building Material Sector Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 14 (Xinhua) -- China's building-material
equipment and machinery sector has made great progress during the
past 18 years, today's "China Daily" reports.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-based English newspaper quotes Lian Jisan, chairman
of the China Building Material Machinery Industry Association, as
saying that the sector relied on imports until the 1980s and it
now includes scientific research, design and manufacture featuring
large scale and special technologies.
</P>
<P>
The introduction of advanced overseas technology has narrowed
the technology gap between China and other countries and has
contributed to the development of the building material industry.
</P>
<P>
The use of cement dry process production equipment with a daily
capacity of 2,000 tons and the float glass production line with a
daily capacity of 500 tons is a sign that China has reached a new
level in adjusting its production mix, Lian says.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, China has been exporting complete plants to produce
cement to Pakistan, Malaysia and Southeast Asian countries. The
proportion of local personnel operating the exported facilities
reached over 80 percent. China aims to enhance the localization of
the imported equipment and building machinery.
</P>
<P>
The rate for cement production equipment with a daily
production capacity of 2,000 tons will reach 90 percent and that
with a daily production capacity of 4,000 tons will reach 85
percent by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
To strengthen the exchanges between the Chinese technicians and
manufactureers and their foreign counterparts, an international
exhibition on cement technology and equipment will be held between
June 16 and 19 in Beijing, the paper says.  
</P>
</TEXT>
