<HEADLINE> UN Reiterates Support for Special Commission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 13 (xinhua) -- The United Nations Security
Council today issued a presidential statement, reiterating its
support for the U.N. Special Commission disarming Iraq and urging
Iraq to ensure the security of the personnel of the commission.
</P>
<P>
Expressing its serious concern at the recent incidents in which
Iraq interfered with helicopter flights operating in support of
inspection of sites designated by the Special Commission, the
council urged Iraq to take effective steps immediately to put an
end to all such actions.
</P>
<P>
The council reminded Iraq of its obligations under the relevant
resolutions of the council and affirmed Iraq was obliged to ensure
the security of the personnel of the Special Commission and to
permit their freedom of movement.
</P>
<P>
Under the Security Council's resolutions of 687, 707 and 715,
Iraq must destroy all its biological, chemical weapons and
ballistic missiles. The U.N. Special Commission was established to
monitor Iraq to implement the resolutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
