<HEADLINE> Arrears to UN Amounts to 2.44 Bln Dlrs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Outstanding contributions
to the United Nations amounted to 2.448 billion dollars as of May
31, UN spokesman Fred Ackhard said here today.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, arrears to the regular budget stood at 743
million dollars and that to the peacekeeping operations at 1,693
million dollars. The International Tribunals were owed 9 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Among the major contributors, the dues back of the United
States alone came to 1,468 million dollars, nearly 60 percent of
the total.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Congress recently discussed a bill on paying 819 million
dollars of U.S. arrears in three years with a number of conditions,
including a string of U.N. spending cuts, a reduction in U.S.
annual contributions and other concessions.
</P>
<P>
UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan said here Thursday that the
U.S. Congress could not legislate for the UN because the other 184
member states might not accept the conditions for paying the back
dues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
