<HEADLINE> UN Calls on Israel to Pay Qana Damages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The General Assembly today
endorsed a resolution calling on Israel to pay nearly 1.8 million
dollars for damage resulting from its shelling of a U.N. base in
southern Lebanon last year.
</P>
<P>
By a vote of 66 in favor to 2 against (Israel, the United
States), with 59 abstentions, the assembly adopted operative
paragraph 8 of the text on financing the United Nations Interim
Force in Lebanon (UNIFIL), which states that Israel shall bear the
responsibility for some 1.8 million dollars as the costs resulting
from the 18 April 1996 incident at UNIFIL headquarters at Qana,
Lebanon. In the incident about 100 civilians taking refuge were
killed.
</P>
<P>
The assembly then adopted the financing resolution as a whole,
by a vote of 127 in favor to 2 against (Israel, the United
States), with 1 abstention from Russia.
</P>
<P>
Israel rejected the decision, calling it "fundamentally flawed
and unprecedented," and said it was not morally or legally bound
to pay.
</P>
<P>
The UNIFIL budget for the 12-month period from July 1, 1997 to
June 30, 1998 is more than 126 million dollars, including the sum
charged to Israel. The peacekeeping operation, established in
1978, comprises some 4,500 troops and 490 civilians.
</P>
<P>
A U.N. inquiry last year found that Israel's shelling of the
Qana camp during a drive against Hizbollah guerrillas who had
fired rockets into northern Israel was unlikely to have been the
result of gross technical or procedural errors, though that could
not be completely ruled out.
</P>
<P>
The General Assembly today appropriated over 850 million
dollars gross for the budgets of a dozen active peacekeeping
operations for the period from 1 July 1997 to 30 June 1996.
</P>
<P>
The amount reflects a substantial drop from the more 1.2
billion dollars sought for the previous 12 months period. All the
two dozen draft texts were approved without a vote, with exception
of that on the financing of the UNIFIL. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
